Narriba","guid":"rFM95mQdtUa21JLGg9q6Sg","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"-30º y 90º\\NNormal","guid":"wLEYifGmVEGxfK-At-7DwQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"167","text":"DI(BI) arriba\\NDIII(BD) abajo","guid":"zYK5I-wgk0yKpuiWHVAn5w","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"-90º y -30º\\NDesviado a la izquierda","guid":"Ci8mg7yXzEe7eN1fjh7_lA","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"167","text":"DI(BI) abajo\\NDIII(BD) arriba","guid":"hHq_pRXgiEGkidPqqbY2aA","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"90º y 180º\\NDesviado a la derecha.","guid":"SXHNFcJ79kGD3M9LHqx7Mg","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"DII\\NSeveridad","guid":"aS0P2PycnE-Xx_l8vRtu6A","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"(+)\\NLeve","guid":"OzC-kdC0nEaF6PnjpZmC_g","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"(iso)\\NModerado","guid":"s_lB6LuoVUuHIpn_NIdJcQ","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"174","text":"(-)\\NGrave","guid":"neDMERmMJkKBQ1VZMp6kgg","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"178","parent":"149","text":"Alteraciones\\Ndel eje","guid":"CbXgA8nqWvldCLcjovoO8A","children":[{"id":"179","parent":"178","text":"DEI\\N<-30°\\NDIII S>R","guid":"hUn45cMcv-ouDhhb4y6wIA","children":[{"id":"180","parent":"179","text":"Etiologías","guid":"myE9BzGmvs2E3N9nzcJicA","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"HVI","guid":"ORPZHnAr3auazoBi6INEgw","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"180","text":"BRI","guid":"UzHw5PiEMZZ06DDyMJ6T_Q","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"180","text":"IM inferior.","guid":"tOFp5EpkowOU4NZ64rUkvw","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"180","text":"WPW","guid":"jrT09Fce49EssL8MHN00Ow","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"180","text":"Bloqueo FAI\\N-45° a -90°","guid":"Mu86nQs_VHJRkTW-tVDqXg","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"qR en aVL","guid":"9D4kU5FfUIisLdFhoAY3pQ","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"185","text":"QRS <0,12\\N4c","guid":"PFYbWEO_rHEQYzaskckC7w","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"185","text":"Sin otra causa","guid":"rRRXUiQDAIobHnqjvqXcGg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"178","text":"DED\\N>90°\\NDI S>R","guid":"9pWYwB90Wk_8x6W2ikJgXA","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"Etiologías","guid":"1jnY9A_gtHRhJU741orEIw","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"EP","guid":"GvdfJommbmpuNy1ZyuhaMQ","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"190","text":"IM lateral","guid":"C9nRPsZqhR8wPsNqSz4VJQ","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"190","text":"Defecto tabique","guid":"uYHrm8mhm30xm5eZVlgOig","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"190","text":"HVD","guid":"qnoBjNp7p5i15Vrho2UNEg","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"190","text":"WPW","guid":"pyUZAcUBcCNPSL4OD9pBmw","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"190","text":"EPOC\\N<110°","guid":"SGFAGOXlNOX9oQLMnlYqJw","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"190","text":"Bloqueo FPI\\N90° a 180°","guid":"43XsvpOyLCNhP93SjaDUCw","children":[{"id":"198","parent":"197","text":"rS","guid":"VA-NpbIMgfNP2BzSd_Nm-g","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"DI","guid":"pSEdLNvQF5a_MGsg7SHBtg","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"aVL","guid":"rLARvhSujToLJXKBRkEPSQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"201","parent":"197","text":"QRS <0,12s\\N4c","guid":"4nTom6Sa9W5AT6dZ-4lcOA","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"197","text":"Sin otra causa","guid":"_kbNIIBF8lZ08zMYKwsVNg","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"197","text":"Hemibloqueos","guid":"hUi7s1U13aGI7HTY5Ra8-w","children":[]}]}]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"278","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"7E37E6BA3EB24F0AAE368CD8","children":[{"id":"279","parent":"278","text":"MÉTODO SISTEMÁTICO DE LECTURA ECG — 5 PASOS: 1) Datos paciente + contexto clínico, 2) Calidad técnica (estándar 1mV=10mm, artefactos), 3) Ritmo (sinusal vs no sinusal), 4) Frecuencia cardíaca, 5) Eje eléctrico. NUNCA interpretar sin el paso 1 — el contexto clínico TRANSFORMA la interpretación","guid":"B63CE854BB5440358FB69095","children":[]},{"id":"280","parent":"278","text":"RITMO SINUSAL: onda P positiva en DI, DII y aVF; negativa en aVR; TODA P seguida de QRS. Eje P entre 0° y +90°. PR constante 120-200ms","guid":"2EA34631C6994205B53C42CC","children":[]},{"id":"281","parent":"278","text":"FRECUENCIA CARDÍACA REGULAR: regla de 300/número de cuadros grandes entre QRS. Irregular: contar QRS en 30 cuadros grandes × 10 = lpm","guid":"89226314981B4488B7ED6B84","children":[]},{"id":"282","parent":"278","text":"EJE QRS: normal entre -30° y +90°. Desviación izquierda (−30° a −90°): HVI, HBAI, infarto inferior. Desviación derecha (+90° a +180°): HVD, HBPI, TEP, cor pulmonale","guid":"80DDCAE26C0B4EF3A169C5D1","children":[]},{"id":"283","parent":"278","text":"BLOQUEOS DE RAMA: BRD (QRS ≥120ms + rSR' en V1 + S ancha en I y V6); BRI (QRS ≥120ms + R ancha y muesca en I, aVL, V5-V6 + ausencia q lateral). BRI NUEVO con clínica → descartar SCA SIEMPRE","guid":"EFCA0E83FF1743978D51435D","children":[]},{"id":"284","parent":"278","text":"CRITERIOS DE SGARBOSSA: BRI + elevación ST ≥1mm concordante (4 puntos), depresión ST ≥1mm en V1-V3 (3 puntos), elevación ST ≥5mm discordante (2 puntos). Score ≥3 → infarto con BRI","guid":"9F3C29A5E03F4E39B6C02009","children":[]},{"id":"285","parent":"278","text":"HIPERTROFIA VENTRICULAR IZQUIERDA (HVI): Sokolow-Lyon: S(V1) + R(V5/V6) >35mm ó R(aVL) >11mm. Cornell: R(aVL) + S(V3) >28mm (H) ó >20mm (M). Especificidad >90% pero sensibilidad baja (~50%)","guid":"1DC071D923334D8AB29173B2","children":[]},{"id":"286","parent":"278","text":"QT CORREGIDO (QTc): Fórmula Bazett QTc=QT/√RR. NORMAL <440ms (H), <460ms (M). PROLONGADO: riesgo TdP con fármacos (amiodarona, antipsicóticos, macrólidos, fluoroquinolonas, metadona)","guid":"B4819CB038B141FC84E11351","children":[]},{"id":"287","parent":"278","text":"ECG EN GERIATRÍA: cambios normales del envejecimiento incluyen PR ligeramente prolongado, QRS de menor voltaje, T aplanadas en precordiales, eje más a la izquierda por cambios postulares. No siempre son patológicos","guid":"EA400FA49C204EC4BC18A3FE","children":[]},{"id":"288","parent":"278","text":"ARTEFACTOS MÁS FRECUENTES: temblor de Parkinson → simula flutter auricular en DIII; electrodos invertidos (DI negativo) → descartar dextrocardia vs inversión de electrodos comparando con V4-V6","guid":"C5540B543AA04C9AB817A2F4","children":[]},{"id":"289","parent":"278","text":"Referencias","guid":"0346D15E3D544232904901F6","children":[{"id":"290","parent":"289","text":"1. Surawicz B et al. AHA/ACCF/HRS Recommendations for the Standardization and Interpretation of the ECG. Circulation. 2009;119(10):e235-e240.","guid":"5A71CBAD64754FFFB9384B4C","children":[]},{"id":"291","parent":"289","text":"2. Sgarbossa EB et al. ECG diagnosis of AMI in LBBB. N Engl J Med. 1996;334(8):481-487.","guid":"96A02ADC334A4CD388F1867D","children":[]},{"id":"292","parent":"289","text":"3. Smith SW et al. Diagnosis of ST-elevation MI in LBBB using Sgarbossa criteria. Ann Emerg Med. 2012;60(6):766-776.","guid":"964A493C3AAA4E90AF10C576","children":[]},{"id":"293","parent":"289","text":"4. Hancock EW et al. AHA/ACCF/HRS Recommendations: Intraventricular Conduction Disturbances. Circulation. 2009;119(10):e235.","guid":"90DF894B6CCF4FE0B51BF9D2","children":[]},{"id":"294","parent":"289","text":"5. Koplan BA et al. ECG changes in normal aging. J Cardiovasc Electrophysiol. 2010;21(5):563-566.","guid":"68A6F299D2794704821B1DF1","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":294,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Estudios Pivotales","folder":"Estudios Pivotales","filename":"The Lancet→ Primer paper sobre el cuidado de personas mayores  copia-2024","id":"map_180","resolved_references":[]}